Windows: each App has one Single Process

Linux: Every app has multiple PID (Process ID)
       Ex,  Firefox app  can be used in browsing, Donwloading, Uploading, Stream
            and if the Download Tap corrupted, then you can kill the process that specified for the Downloading 


Kernel: Responsible for Hardware Management
        to Execute Process or Not.




Processes:-

in Linux every app contain multiple PID and PPID (Parent Process ID)

                                                PPID
                                                  |
                                            PID 1    PID2

PPID : Generate/Terminate Child PID
       Assign Resources for the PID so the Child PID can do the task


pstree =>> Process List as a Tree
